            . I live in Shire-lane, Temple bar, and am a <rs id="t17700117-15-viclabel106" type="occupation">printer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17700117-15-victim230 t17700117-15-viclabel106"></join>. On the <rs id="t17700117-15-cd107" type="crimeDate">16th of December</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17700117-15-off105 t17700117-15-cd107"></join>, I was in the <placeName id="t17700117-15-crimeloc108">Fleet-market</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17700117-15-crimeloc108" type="placeName" value="Fleet-market"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17700117-15-crimeloc108" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17700117-15-off105 t17700117-15-crimeloc108"></join>, between nine and ten o'clock at night. I stopped to see a man that was in liquor buying some china; the prisoner stood by me. As soon as he was gone, I missed my handkerchief: I followed and saw him behind a green-stall looking at it. I collared him, and he dropped it down; I took it up; (Produced and deposed to.) this was about twenty yards from the place where we had been standing together. I took him to the watch-house; there he said it was the first fact that ever he committed.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I had been standing to see the man buy some things, and was going to get a pint of beer. He came and said I had picked his pocket. I never saw him in my life before; neither did I ever see his handkerchief. I am a <rs id="t17700117-15-deflabel109" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17700117-15-defend228 t17700117-15-deflabel109"></join> in the Fleet-market.</p>
               <p>He called 
